In [[mathematics]], more precisely in [[algebra]], an '''étale group scheme''' is a certain kind of [[group scheme]].

== Definition ==
A finite [[group scheme]] <math>G</math> over a [[field (mathematics)|field]] <math>K</math> is called an ''étale group scheme'' if it is represented by an [[étale algebra|étale K-algebra]] <math>\mathfrak{R}</math>, i.e. if <math>\mathfrak{R}\otimes _{K}\bar{K}</math> is [[isomorphic]] to <math>\bar{K}\times ...\times\bar{K}</math>.

